## ⚠️ CRITICAL RULES

- **SlintORM only** — never use Prisma, Drizzle, or raw SQL directly. All DB access through SlintORM models
- **No external plugin purchases** — if a feature exists, build it in. Never suggest a third-party SaaS as the solution
- **Per-seat pricing is forbidden** — the billing model is contact/branch based, unlimited users always
- **Every API route must** check the user's workspace and role before returning any data (row-level security via workspaceId)
- **Soft delete everything** important — contacts, deals, products, employees, social accounts
- **All social tokens** must be encrypted at rest befor
at rest before storing in the database
- **TypeScript strict mode** throughout — no `any` types

Begin by setting up SlintORM (lib/db.ts) with all models defined and migrated, then implement the NextAuth system with Google and Facebook providers. Confirm both are working before moving to dashboards.




